The paper deals with the problem of quickest event detection in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines. However, the focus on sleep-wake scheduling and energy conservation suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of sequential decision processes and optimization techniques further supports this classification. Additionally, the use of sensor networks and communication protocols suggests that the paper may also be classified under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of statistical methods and probability theory suggests that the paper may also be classified under cs.MA (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
